reviews.text:
It is a cheesecake with lime and strawberry right on top. &#xD;
&#xD;
I thought the FA Distilled Lime was an odd choice, given other options like VT Persian Lime or FA Florida Key Lime, but limes can be tricky and maybe those were tried and just didn’t do as good a job of putting the lime on the cheesecake as this one did. It’s a bit like pouring lime soda on a cheesecake rather than a slice of lime, but the alternatives might well have been a worse result. FLV Lime Wedge would have been perfect if it weren’t so damned fadey.  &#xD;
&#xD;
All the elements are there, the thick, slightly tangy cheesecake, a little crust, the fruits esp the fresh strawberry. It’s a recipe that works. &#xD;
